Reasoning: The paper deals with Generalized Degrees of Freedom (GDoF) characterizations of wireless interference channels (IC) and broadcast channels (BC) under the assumption of finite precision channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT). This falls under the domain of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also explores the possibility of an extremal network theory, which is related to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the GDoF benefits of transmitter cooperation, which is related to Signal Processing (cs.SP).
